<br>
Example 1: Dvinn in CB can be kept on one side of the moat while you nuke from the other = Exploit<br>
<br>
Example 2: The Gargoyles in MM will float around the lake allowing you to side step and force them to fly all the way around the lake again allowing you to get off a few more spells. = Exploit<br>
<br>
Example 3: You can make skeletons in Nakena run around the room allowing you to cast on them by side stepping ina few places = Exploit.<br>
<br>
Now is it fair that using the bad pathing to your advantage is an exploit? No, but its the way it is.<br>
<br>
And before someone pops off and tells me these arent exploits, I have watched people get warning fro the GM's for it so they are considered exploits. <br>
